  Used to recruit migrant workers for all employment 
groups, except female domestic workers.
  The migrant worker bears the full cost of the recruit -
ment. The costs are either paid to the agent or paid 
directly to the relevant institution. 
  Workers mostly resort to informal loans from family 
and friends to bear such costs.83
  Costs include: 
a. SLBFE registration fee; 
b. Visa cost;
c. Migrant’s training fee; 
d. Medical certificate;
e. Insurance cost;
f. Advertising costs of the agency;
g. Airfare;
h. Transportation (both domestic and overseas); 
and
i. Costs borne by the agencies for any dispute 
resolution;

